This paper deals with the automated verification of trust in multiagent systems, which involves reasoning about mental attitudes such as beliefs, goals, and intentions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on stochastic multiplayer games, which are a type of game theory, indicating that the paper may also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also deals with temporal logic, which is a topic in Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Furthermore, the paper is concerned with multiagent systems, which suggests that it may belong to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with trust, which is a topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
